                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/393: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Piles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-19T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Department’s 22, May 17, 7 p.m., my 31, May 17, 11 a.m. President will
                    suspend action as requested in the Department’s memorandum until final decision
                    of Supreme Court. Prefers, however, to suspend it on petition of company
                    interested, which I have asked lawyers to file <pb facs="0713" n="595"
                        xml:id="pg_595"/> Monday next. Decree will be suspended about Tuesday.
                    President accordingly has returned my memorandum. President and Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs were attentive. Full particulars by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Piles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
